WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:03.913
You asking me if I ever
had a gun to my head?

00:04.127 --> 00:05.187
Which time?

00:05.235 --> 00:06.656
No, this never happen to me.

00:06.711 --> 00:09.580
It was surprising. I'd never
been so calm in all my life.

00:09.589 --> 00:11.222
I threw my wallet
at the guy and ran away.

00:11.225 --> 00:12.294
I remember that it happened,

00:12.318 --> 00:13.984
but I can't tell you
anything about it,

00:14.125 --> 00:15.293
except I can describe the gun

00:15.349 --> 00:17.447
down to the scratch
on the barrel.

00:17.512 --> 00:19.495
Gun to your head,
what would you do?

00:19.513 --> 00:21.328
Kept hearing those words.

00:21.393 --> 00:23.147
I thought it was
a great opportunity.

00:23.195 --> 00:28.065
After all,
crisis reveals character.

00:31.644 --> 00:33.199
Good morning, everyone.

00:33.246 --> 00:34.834
Hi, uh, I'm chunk Palmer.

00:34.881 --> 00:36.736
I'll be your liaison
for the day.

00:36.783 --> 00:39.438
We here at tac are aware
that you have many options.

00:39.485 --> 00:40.615
Of how you spend your time

00:40.662 --> 00:42.708
and we appreciate
you spending it with us.

00:42.755 --> 00:44.419
You all have been carefully selected

00:44.466 --> 00:46.412
to participate in today's mock jury.

00:46.459 --> 00:48.556
It's an opportunity to express
your thoughts and feel...

00:48.603 --> 00:50.661
Smells good.
What is that, coffee?

00:51.364 --> 00:52.518
I miss coffee so much.

00:52.565 --> 00:53.995
There's a little left
if you want some.

00:54.042 --> 00:55.287
Oh, you're sweet, but, uh,

00:55.334 --> 00:56.497
it's not good for my ticker.

00:56.544 --> 00:57.799
I got a heart thing.

00:57.846 --> 00:59.633
All for $200 a day.

00:59.643 --> 01:00.993
And a hot lunch.

01:01.040 --> 01:02.970
So, uh, please,
let's get out of this rain.

01:03.017 --> 01:04.375
Please follow me.

01:06.646 --> 01:08.142
As we proceed through
the security checkpoint,

01:08.189 --> 01:09.368
if you look to your left,

01:09.415 --> 01:11.713
you might catch a glimpse
of one of our analysts

01:11.760 --> 01:13.272
in their natural habitat.

01:13.319 --> 01:14.849
The indispensable tac employees,

01:14.896 --> 01:16.451
Cable Mccrory and Danny James.

01:16.498 --> 01:17.610
Hi, everyone.

01:17.657 --> 01:19.554
I always wanted to be
in one of these focus groups.

01:19.601 --> 01:23.115
I mean, I'm not a white male
aged 18 to 49,

01:23.215 --> 01:24.851
but I remember what
I liked when I was.

01:24.912 --> 01:27.495
Before we settle in
to our new home in mock court,

01:27.612 --> 01:30.537
now might be a good time
for a bathroom break.

